Preheat your oven to 220°C. Pour a glug of oil onto a #baking tray{} and pop in your oven.

> Heating up the baking tray and oil = crispy potatoes!

Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil on high heat with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Peel the @potatoes{450%g}(peeled), chop them into 3cm chunks. Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook for ~{5-6%mins} or until the edges have softened when you poke them with a knife.

Meanwhile, halve and peel the @red onion{1}(halved). Chop each half into 4 pieces. Trim the @carrot{2}(trimmed), halve lengthways then chop each strip lengthways into 3 strips. Chop into batons. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}.

Once the potatoes are ready, drain them in a #colander{}, pop them back in the pan, then sprinkle on the @plain flour{8%g}. Give your pan a shake to fluff up the potato.

> Doing this gives your potato edges more surface area, so they'll be crispier.

Take your hot baking tray out of your oven, gently tip the potatoes onto it in a single layer - careful not to burn yourself on any hot oil. Season with salt and turn the potatoes in the oil.

Roast the potatoes on the top shelf of your oven for ~{30-40%mins}, turning halfway through. Next, pop the carrots and onion onto a separate baking tray, drizzle with oil, a pinch of salt and @black pepper{}, the @ground cumin{1%tsp} and half the @honey{15%ml}. Toss to coat, roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{20-25%mins}.

Meanwhile, heat a #saucepan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). When hot, add the @flaked almonds{25%g}, toast until golden, ~{2-3%mins}. Turn frequently and watch them like a hawk! Transfer to a #bowl{}.

Pop your pan back on medium-high heat. Add a drizzle of oil and the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%mins}. Drain off any excess fat. Add the garlic, cook for ~{1%minute} more. Remove from the heat. Add the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}, remaining @honey{15%ml} and a drizzle of oil. Stir together.

Once the carrots and onion are soft, remove from the oven, lay the @chopped kale{100%g} on top, drizzle with oil, a pinch of salt and pepper. Bake until crispy, ~{4-5%mins} then remove from the oven. Add the roast potatoes to the veg along with the lardons and dressing. Toss together, then serve in bowls. Sprinkle over the toasted almonds and enjoy!